article.headline: Cavey shirks ankle injury for 19 points
article.linkText: Cavey's second-half run boosts No. 19 Iowa
article.story:
CHAMPAIGN, Ill. (AP) -- Jamie Cavey scored seven of her 19 points
during a 14-7 second-half run to lead Iowa (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today; No. 18 AP) past Illinois
72-58 Sunday.

Cavey had only two points at halftime after spending several
minutes on the bench with an ankle injury, but she was 8-of-10 from
the field and 1-for-1 from the free-throw line after the break.

The Hawkeyes (13-0, 2-0 Big Ten), playing their third game in
six days, also got 12 points from Crystal Smith and 10 from Tiffany
Reedy. Iowa is off to its best start since the 1987-88 team won its
first 22 games.

Illinois (9-3, 1-1) led only briefly in the first half but was
down by only seven, 41-34, at the break. An 8-5 Illinois run to
start the second half closed the gap to 46-41, but Cavey's 3-point
play with 15:28 to go started Iowa's decisive run.

Tiffanie Guthrie led Illinois with 18 points, who were 0-12 from
3-point range. Erin Wigley scored 14 and Angelina Williams had 12
as the Illini had their five-game winning streak snapped.
